Does it make sense to make the law even more stringent?
I don't think so.
The system must exclude those who want to attack and abuse the system, and not punish those who have committed a form error that does not affect the actual decision-making.
Such a system simply puts the bureaucracy under even greater pressure.
Where's the way out?
First of all, let’s say which path is not the right one.
The Prime Minister recently said that the SDGs would not deal with controls of the so-called "black system" - what does that mean exactly?
