The award law contains relatively strict rules on the formal execution of certain transactions - and this is also true for the protection of public competition.
On the other hand, however, it is also tragic if the provider with the best offer is excluded only due to form errors.
The law will never be perfect, but it has to be applied correctly – and that is what I think is missing from us.
